terms.medium_def:
A man from the tribe of Judah living at the time of Egypt and Wilderness, only mentioned at 1Ch.2.48; 
only referred to as Sheber (שֶׁ֫בֶר); 
son of Caleb and Maacah; 
a brother of Tirhanah, Regem(?), Jotham(?), Geshan(?), Pelet(?), Ephah(?), Shaaph(?), Shaaph and Sheva; 
half-brother of: Hur, Jesher, Shobab, Ardon, Mesha, Haran, Moza, Gazez and Achsah. § a Judaite, son of Caleb by his concubine Maachah and of the family of Hezron
